article.headline: James Madison 41, Delaware 7
article.story: HARRISONBURG, Va. -- Rodney Landers rushed for 185 yards and two touchdowns to lead James Madison to a 41-7 victory over Delaware on Saturday. The Dukes (8-1, 6-0 Colonial Athletic Association) rolled up 385 yards of offense to win their eighth consecutive game. Landers, who was 6 of 12 for 62 yards passing, scored on a 1-yard run in the second quarter and added a 35-yard touchdown run in the third, when James Madison stretched its lead to 34-7. He has 1,115 yards rushing this season. Jerry Butler scored on a 94-yard kickoff return with 36 seconds remaining in the third quarter for Delaware (3-6, 1-4). Eugene Holloman and Jamal Sullivan also scored on the ground for James Madison and Scotty McGee returned a punt 64 yards for another score. Drew Dudzik added the Dukes' final touchdown on a 5-yard touchdown pass to Charlie Newman with 10:02 remaining in the game. Delaware was held to 169 yards of offense and 10 first downs.
